step.tex:
\begin{align}

\dfrac{\cos 2 x+2\sin^2 x}{\cos^ 2 x} \,
&= \dfrac{\cos 2 x+(1 - \cos 2x)}{\cos^ 2 x} \\
&= \dfrac{1}{\cos^2 x} \\
&= \sec^2 x 
\end{align}

\begin{align}
\dfrac{\cos 2 x+2\sin^2 x}{\cos^ 2 x} \, &= \sec^2 x \\ \implies
\int \dfrac{\cos 2 x+2\sin^2 x}{\cos^ 2 x} \, dx &= \int \sec^2 x \, dx \\ &= \tan x+C \end{align}

\begin{align}
\dfrac{\cos 2 x+2\sin^2 x}{\cos^ 2 x} \, &= \sec^2 x \\ \implies
\int \dfrac{\cos 2 x+2\sin^2 x}{\cos^ 2 x} \, dx &= \int \sec^2 x \, dx \\ &= \tan^2 x+C \end{align}
